race.comment: A good contest. DAYTONA DIVA (2) was quickly back on track, winning the Strutt Stakes comfortably from the speed. She's likely to roll over and position forward and is up to repeating the dose. CRACK THE SHUTTERS (1) improved again when narrowly beaten in the Launceston Guineas, backed into red figures. She also races forward and has been freshened 37 days. Deserves to crack one of these and deserves another chance. AURORA RISE (5) leads the Victorian charge. Followed the Geelong Maiden win with a 1.8L defeat in the Strutt and will improve off that. Keeps John Allen and can feature with average luck in the run. KAZARU (4) impressed winning her Maiden at Sale and is sure to appreciate the middle distance. In her previous preparation she competed strongly at Stakes and Group level over 1400m in Adelaide, suggesting she has the class.
